HEADWORD: Chondrodite
<hw>Chon"dro*dite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>cho`ndros</grk> a grain (of wheat or spelt), cartilage.]</ety>
<fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A fluosilicate of magnesia and iron, yellow to
red in color, often occurring in granular form in a crystalline
limestone.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

